tldr: The user requested to add a database and an admin dashboard to a sleep
  questionnaire application. The agent implemented a PostgreSQL database with
  Prisma, created API routes for responses and CSV export, and built a simple
  password-protected admin dashboard. The authentication system was later
  simplified using Next.js middleware.
overview: The user aimed to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by adding
  persistent data storage and a client-facing admin dashboard. The agent began
  by evaluating the existing codebase and then developed a comprehensive plan.
  Key steps included updating demographic data fields, defining a Prisma schema
  for questionnaire responses, creating API endpoints for data submission and
  retrieval (including CSV export), and building a simple admin dashboard with
  login functionality. A crucial decision point involved the authentication
  system; initially, a custom session management was implemented, but it was
  later simplified to leverage Next.js middleware for more streamlined route
  protection and a basic cookie-based authentication, which was more suitable
  for the project's requirements. The outcome is a functional system capable of
  storing questionnaire data, providing an administrative interface, and
  offering data export capabilities, with clear instructions provided for
  database setup and migration.
